    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Predicting the Eredivisie using a Bayesian Approach\"\ndate: 2026-05-26\ndate-format: \"D MMM YYYY\"\nformat: \n  revealjs\n---\n\n\n## Introduction\n\n- Predicting match outcomes\n\n## About\n\n- Eredivisie consists of $T = 18$ teams\n  - Each team play twice against each other team\n- There are $G = 306$ games\n\n## Model\n\n- The goals scored in the $g$-th game by the home and away team are:\n$$y_{g,1}, \\quad\\text{and}\\quad y_{g,2}$$\n\n- These are counts, and can take values $0, 1, \\ldots$, typically modelled as following a Poisson distribution\n$$y_{g,j} \\mid \\theta_{g,j} \\sim \\mathrm{Poisson}(\\theta_{g,j})$$ with the parameters $\\theta_{g,j}$ representing the scoring intensity in the $g$-th game for the team playing at home ($j=1$) and away ($j=2$), respectively.\n\n- The parameters assume a log-linear random effect model:\n$$\\begin{align}\n\\log\\left(\\theta_{g,1}\\right) &= \\eta + \\alpha_{h[g]} + \\delta_{a[g]} \\\\\n\\log\\left(\\theta_{g,2}\\right) &= \\alpha_{a[g]} + \\delta_{h[g]} \n\\end{align}$$\n\n## Priors\n\nWe assume the following priors:\n$$\n\\begin{align}\n\\eta &\\sim \\mathrm{Normal}(0, 0.0001) \\\\\n\\alpha_{t} &\\sim \\mathrm{Normal}(\\mu_{\\alpha}, \\tau_{\\alpha}) \\\\\n\\delta_{t} &\\sim \\mathrm{Normal}(\\mu_{\\delta}, \\tau_{\\delta})\n\\end{align}\n$$\n\nWe specify identifiability constrains, i.e., sum-to-zero constraint:\n$$\\sum_{t=1}^{T}\\alpha_{t} = 0, \\quad \\sum_{t=1}^{T}\\delta_{t} = 0$$\n\nWe define the following hyperpriors:\n$$\n\\begin{align}\n\\mu_{\\alpha} &\\sim \\mathrm{Normal}(0, 0.0001), &\\quad \\mu_{\\delta} &\\sim \\mathrm{Normal}(0, 0.0001) \\\\\n\\tau_{\\alpha} &\\sim \\mathrm{Gamma}(0.1, 0.1), &\\quad \\tau_{\\delta} &\\sim \\mathrm{Gamma}(0.1, 0.1)\n\\end{align}\n$$\n\n## Data\n\n::: {#990e2b0c .cell execution_count=1}\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=7}\n```{=html}\n<div>\n<style scoped>\n    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n        vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n        vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe thead th {\n        text-align: right;\n    }\n</style>\n<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th></th>\n      <th>Div</th>\n      <th>Date</th>\n      <th>Time</th>\n      <th>HomeTeam</th>\n      <th>AwayTeam</th>\n      <th>FTHG</th>\n      <th>FTAG</th>\n      <th>FTR</th>\n      <th>HTHG</th>\n      <th>HTAG</th>\n      <th>...</th>\n      <th>AvgC&lt;2.5</th>\n      <th>AHCh</th>\n      <th>B365CAHH</th>\n      <th>B365CAHA</th>\n      <th>PCAHH</th>\n      <th>PCAHA</th>\n      <th>MaxCAHH</th>\n      <th>MaxCAHA</th>\n      <th>AvgCAHH</th>\n      <th>AvgCAHA</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>N1</td>\n      <td>05/08/2022</td>\n      <td>19:00</td>\n      <td>Heerenveen</td>\n      <td>Sparta Rotterdam</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>D</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>...</td>\n      <td>1.83</td>\n      <td>-0.50</td>\n      <td>1.86</td>\n      <td>2.04</td>\n      <td>1.86</td>\n      <td>2.05</td>\n      <td>1.91</td>\n      <td>2.05</td>\n      <td>1.87</td>\n      <td>1.96</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>N1</td>\n      <td>06/08/2022</td>\n      <td>15:30</td>\n      <td>For Sittard</td>\n      <td>Ajax</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>3</td>\n      <td>A</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>...</td>\n      <td>3.23</td>\n      <td>1.75</td>\n      <td>2.04</td>\n      <td>1.86</td>\n      <td>2.01</td>\n      <td>1.88</td>\n      <td>2.08</td>\n      <td>1.89</td>\n      <td>2.01</td>\n      <td>1.84</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>N1</td>\n      <td>06/08/2022</td>\n      <td>17:45</td>\n      <td>Cambuur</td>\n      <td>Excelsior</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>A</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td